    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Discrete Fourier Transform\"\ndescription: \"Decompose any time series into its frequency components. Full derivation, NumPy implementation, and a real price-signal example.\"\ndate: 2026-04-01\ncategories: [signal-processing, math]\n---\n\n## Motivation\n\nPrice time series contain overlapping periodic patterns — intraday rhythms, weekly seasonality,\nnews shocks. The **Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT)** lets us decompose a signal into its\nconstituent frequencies and measure their strength.\n\n---\n\n## The Math\n\nGiven a discrete signal $x_0, x_1, \\dots, x_{N-1}$, the DFT produces $N$ complex coefficients:\n\n$$\nX_k = \\sum_{n=0}^{N-1} x_n \\cdot e^{-i 2\\pi k n / N}, \\quad k = 0, 1, \\dots, N-1\n$$\n\nThe **power spectrum** — how much energy lives at each frequency — is:\n\n$$\nP_k = \\frac{|X_k|^2}{N}\n$$\n\nThe corresponding frequency for bin $k$ given a sampling rate $f_s$ is:\n\n$$\nf_k = \\frac{k \\cdot f_s}{N}\n$$\n\n::: {.callout-note title=\"Why complex numbers?\"}\n$e^{-i 2\\pi k n / N} = \\cos(2\\pi k n/N) - i\\sin(2\\pi k n/N)$. The real part captures\ncosine components, the imaginary part captures sine components. The magnitude $|X_k|$ tells\nyou the total amplitude regardless of phase.\n:::\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n::: {#6ca8a18b .cell execution_count=1}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nimport numpy as np\nimport plotly.graph_objects as go\nfrom plotly.subplots import make_subplots\n\ndef dft_power_spectrum(signal: np.ndarray, sample_rate: float = 1.0):\n    \"\"\"\n    Compute the one-sided power spectrum of a real signal.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    signal      : 1-D array of real values\n    sample_rate : samples per unit time (e.g. 1.0 = one sample per day)\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    freqs : array of frequencies (cycles per unit time)\n    power : array of power values\n    \"\"\"\n    N = len(signal)\n    X = np.fft.rfft(signal)          # rfft exploits real-valued symmetry → N/2+1 bins\n    freqs = np.fft.rfftfreq(N, d=1 / sample_rate)\n    power = (np.abs(X) ** 2) / N\n    return freqs, power\n```\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Example: Synthetic price signal\n\n::: {#07a744ab .cell execution_count=2}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nrng = np.random.default_rng(42)\nN, fs = 512, 1.0          # 512 trading days, 1 sample/day\n\nt = np.arange(N) / fs\nsignal = (\n    np.sin(2 * np.pi * t / 20)   # 20-day cycle\n    + 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * t / 5)  # 5-day cycle\n    + 0.3 * rng.standard_normal(N)      # noise\n)\n\nfreqs, power = dft_power_spectrum(signal, sample_rate=fs)\n\nfig = make_subplots(rows=2, cols=1,\n                    subplot_titles=(\"Synthetic price signal\", \"Power spectrum\"))\n\nfig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=t, y=signal, mode=\"lines\", name=\"signal\",\n                         line=dict(color=\"#4361ee\", width=1)), row=1, col=1)\n\nfig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=1 / freqs[1:], y=power[1:], mode=\"lines\",\n                         name=\"power\", line=dict(color=\"#f72585\")), row=2, col=1)\n\nfig.update_xaxes(title_text=\"Trading day\", row=1)\nfig.update_xaxes(title_text=\"Period (days)\", row=2, type=\"log\")\nfig.update_yaxes(title_text=\"Price\", row=1)\nfig.update_yaxes(title_text=\"Power\", row=2)\nfig.update_layout(height=520, showlegend=False, template=\"simple_white\")\nfig.show()\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div>            <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_SVG\"></script><script>if (window.MathJax && window.MathJax.Hub && window.MathJax.Hub.Config) {window.MathJax.Hub.Config({SVG: {font: \"STIX-Web\"}});}</script>                <script>window.PlotlyConfig = {MathJaxConfig: 'local'};</script>\n        <script charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-3.4.0.min.js\" integrity=\"sha256-KEmPoupLpFyGMyGAiOsiNDbKDKAvxXAn/W+oQa0ZAfk=\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>                <div id=\"1c8a5d1a-102e-4bb3-b8fd-8cdb63466627\" class=\"plo